This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories as it focuses on 3D object detection and tracking in crowded urban scenes using LiDAR sensors. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for this task, which suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a labeling methodology to speed up the annotation process, which could also place it in the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
